The paper discusses the development of a collaborative online laboratory for use in an educational setting, which involves considerations of human-computer interaction (HCI), computer-supported cooperative work (CSCW), and computer-supported collaborative learning (CSCL). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC, which focuses on HCI. The second most likely sub-category is cs.CSCW, which deals with the design and use of technology to support collaborative work. The third most likely sub-category is cs.CSCL, which focuses on the use of technology to support collaborative learning. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.CL, which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics, as the paper may involve the analysis of language used in the collaborative online laboratory. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.EDU, which deals with educational technology and the use of technology in education.
